  "text": "ROS generating capability is one of the characteristics of nanomaterials due to the larger surface area and the increased probability of chemical reactions on surface [CITATION_1] . However, such a characteristic appears to be limited to inorganic nanoparticles. Liposomes or micelles with organic surfaces composed of lipids and polymers did not produce ROS. This was also the case with the mPEG-PDLLA micellar formulation of Nanoxel (Fig. 4) . Presumably, ROS production is not the main concern of nanoformulations in terms of toxicity.",
